## Decisions Made
- Used `/knowledge-distillery:init` skill to bootstrap the full pipeline: Ensures all components (vault, workflows, directives, permissions) are created in a consistent, idempotent manner rather than manual setup.
- Target directive file is AGENTS.md (not CLAUDE.md): CLAUDE.md contains `@AGENTS.md`, so per the init skill's detection logic, AGENTS.md is the correct target.
- All four GitHub Actions workflows created from skill templates: mark-evidence (Stage A on PR merge), batch-refine (Stage B weekly), curate-report (comment-triggered curation), apply-changeset (post-merge vault update).

## Problems Encountered
